 'Start on hands and knees. Tuck toes, lift hips toward the ceiling forming an inverted V. Press hands firmly into the mat, externally rotate the upper arms (rotate the eye of the elbow forward). Straighten legs as much as flexibility allows. Hold 5-10 breaths.',
 'Dumping the weight into the wrists (must distribute through the full hand — spread fingers wide), rounding the upper back (thoracic extension is the goal), hyperextending the knees.',
