('Seated Forward Fold (Paschimottanasana)',
 'hamstrings', array['erectors','calves','glutes'], array['hamstrings','erectors'],
 'yoga_pilates', 'stretch', array['yoga_mat'], 'beginner', false,
 'Sit with legs straight. Flex the feet. Hinge at the hips (not the waist) to reach toward the feet. Hold the feet, shins, or a strap. Lengthen the spine on the inhale, deepen the fold on the exhale. Hold 1-3 minutes.',
 'Rounding from the waist instead of hinging at the hip (creates spinal flexion that limits the hamstring stretch), flexing the feet only to touch the hands to them (the focus is the hamstring and spine, not how low you go), gripping the toes and pulling hard.',
 'yoga',
 array['Sit on a folded blanket if the pelvis tilts backward: this immediately improves the fold quality','Inhale: spine lengthens and lifts slightly. Exhale: fold deeper. This breath rhythm is how yoga changes flexibility over time','Feet flexed: this adds a calf stretch as a bonus while maintaining the hamstring line','A strap around the feet is not a regression — it allows correct hip-hinge mechanics regardless of flexibility'],
 array['Seated Forward Fold with Twist','Advanced Seated Forward Fold'],
 array['Seated Forward Fold with Strap','Knees-Bent Seated Forward Fold'],
