 'yoga_pilates', 'stretch', array['yoga_mat'], 'beginner', false,
 'Lie flat on the back. Let the feet fall naturally outward. Arms slightly away from the body, palms facing up. Close the eyes. Release all muscular effort. Remain completely still for 5-15 minutes. This is the most important pose in yoga.',
 'Leaving early (5 minutes is the minimum — the nervous system integration that occurs during savasana is the entire reason you did the session), fidgeting, keeping the eyes open.',
 'yoga',
 array['This is not rest — it is active integration: the nervous system is consolidating every adaptation from the session','Arms away from the body: this prevents subtle muscular engagement that happens when arms touch the torso','Cover with a blanket: the body temperature drops in savasana — warmth supports deeper relaxation','The goal: conscious awareness without muscular effort. This state, called pratyahara, is the bridge between physical yoga and meditation'],
