 'yoga_pilates', 'extension', array['yoga_mat'], 'advanced', true,
 'Lie on back. Place hands by the ears, fingers pointing toward the shoulders. Feet flat, hip-width apart. Press into hands and feet simultaneously to lift the hips and chest, coming into a full backbend arch. Hold 5 breaths.',
 'Placing hands too wide (must be shoulder-width — wide hands collapse the shoulder girdle), not warming up the spine adequately (camel, bridge, and cobra must precede this pose), pushing through pain in the lower back or wrists.',
