 'yoga_pilates', 'multi_joint', array['yoga_mat'], 'intermediate', false,
 'A 10-minute yin-style sequence targeting the hips: Dragon (2min each side) → Sleeping Swan/Pigeon (2min each side) → Supine Twist (1min each side). Each pose held in stillness, breathing into the sensation.',
 'Moving in and out of the poses repeatedly (yin yoga is about stillness — the magic is in the long hold and continuous breath), treating sensations as something to escape rather than explore.',
 'yoga',
 array['Yin yoga works the connective tissue (fascia, ligaments, joint capsules) — not muscles. Muscle-style effort is counterproductive.','Sensation is information: a dull ache or pressure is normal and productive. Sharp or shooting pain means back off immediately.','The longer the hold, the deeper the change: 2-3 minute holds begin to affect the deeper connective structures that 30-second stretches never reach','This sequence is ideal post-training, post-run, or as a dedicated evening practice'],
