('Pilates Roll Up',
 'rectus_abdominis', array['hip_flexors','erectors','hamstrings'], array['rectus_abdominis','hip_flexors'],
 'yoga_pilates', 'multi_joint', array['yoga_mat'], 'intermediate', false,
 'Lie flat, legs straight, arms overhead. Inhale to begin. Exhale while rolling up vertebra by vertebra — chin to chest, then head, then shoulders, then thoracic, then reaching forward over the legs. Inhale at the top. Exhale to roll back down.',
 'Momentum-based sit-up (must be controlled articulation of each vertebra), holding the breath, not pressing the legs into the floor as a counterbalance.',
 'pilates',
 array['C-curve: the spine creates a perfect C-curve throughout the roll — no straight-spine forward folding','Vertebra by vertebra: the Pilates roll-up is NOT a sit-up. Each spinal joint articulates sequentially, building body awareness the sit-up cannot','Arms provide direction not force: reach forward to feel each vertebra peel off the mat','If this is impossible initially, use a resistance band around the feet: the pull helps articulate the spine correctly'],
 array['Roll Up to Roll Over','Roll Up with Twist'],
 array['Roll Up with Band Assist','Short Roll-Up to Seated'],
