 'yoga_pilates', 'rotation', array['yoga_mat'], 'beginner', false,
 'Lie on back, one leg extended on the floor, other leg pointing toward the ceiling. Circle the raised leg: across the body, down, around, and back up. Make 5-8 circles each direction, then switch legs. Keep the pelvis absolutely still.',
 'The pelvis rocking with each circle (the core must stabilize the pelvis — any movement means the range is too large), bending the raised knee excessively, forgetting to do both directions.',
 'pilates',
 array['The circle size is determined by pelvis stability: make the circle as large as you can while the pelvis remains rock-still','Pressing the floor leg into the mat: this provides proprioceptive feedback about pelvic stability','Both directions: clockwise then counter-clockwise — each direction challenges different hip and inner thigh muscles','A flat back throughout: if the back arches when the leg lowers, reduce the circle size immediately'],
