('Pilates Rolling Like a Ball',
 'erectors', array['core','hamstrings'], array['erectors','core'],
 'yoga_pilates', 'multi_joint', array['yoga_mat'], 'beginner', false,
 'Sit at the edge of your mat. Knees to chest, hands on shins, feet lifted. Round the spine into a C-curve. Inhale to roll back to the shoulder blades. Exhale to roll back up to balance. Do not roll onto the neck.',
 'Rolling onto the neck (must stop at the shoulder blades — the neck is not a landing zone), straightening the spine during the roll (must maintain C-curve throughout), using momentum instead of control.',
 'pilates',
 array['Stop at the shoulder blades: the neck is protected by stopping HERE — practice with a hand behind the neck initially','C-curve maintained: imagine a ball with no flat sides — it rolls evenly because it is round. Your spine must create the same shape','The inhale rocks back, the exhale rocks forward: the breath is the engine of the rolling','Rolling Like a Ball massages the spine and activates the parasympathetic system: it is both therapeutic and playful'],
 array['Open Leg Rocker','Rolling Like a Ball Variations'],
