 'Lie on back, both knees to chest, head and shoulders curled off the floor. Extend one leg to 45°. Place opposite hand on the ankle and same hand on the knee of the bent leg. Switch legs in a pumping rhythm. 10-20 reps total.',
 'Not maintaining the curl of the head and shoulders (they must stay lifted throughout), dropping the extended leg below 45° causing lower back strain, not switching hands with each leg switch.',
