('Pilates Double Leg Stretch',
 'core', array['hip_flexors','deltoids','lats'], array['core','hip_flexors'],
 'yoga_pilates', 'multi_joint', array['yoga_mat'], 'intermediate', false,
 'Lie on back, knees to chest, head and shoulders curled up. Inhale: extend both legs to 45° while reaching arms overhead. Exhale: circle arms around as you hug knees back to chest. Repeat 8-10 times.',
 'Dropping the legs too low (lower back must stay imprinted — 45° or higher until sufficient core strength is developed), not circling the arms (the arm circle engages the lats and creates shoulder mobility work).',
 'pilates',
