 'Pulling the head with the hands (the neck must not flex — it stays long and neutral while the thoracic spine rotates), swinging the elbows instead of rotating the ribcage, rushing the movement.',
 'pilates',
 array['The rotation comes from the ribcage, not the elbow: imagine the bottom rib moving toward the opposite hip bone','Elbows stay wide: if they close toward the head, you are pulling the neck instead of rotating the thoracic spine','Slow is more difficult: slow the rhythm down and feel the oblique contraction rather than using momentum','Criss Cross is simultaneously a hip flexor exercise AND an oblique rotation exercise — targeting both abdominal layers'],
