 'pilates',
 array['The lifted leg is the challenge to the plank stability: resist any rotation or hip shift','Flex the foot of the lifted leg: this activates the glutes and creates the long-leg line required in classical Pilates','Think of pushing the floor away with the standing hands while reaching the heel of the lifted leg backward','This develops the shoulder stability, core endurance, and glute strength to maintain a plank under asymmetric loading'],
