 'yoga_pilates', 'stretch', array['yoga_mat'], 'beginner', false,
 'Sit tall with legs extended, slightly wider than hip-width. Flex feet. Inhale to grow tall. Exhale to reach arms forward and fold, rounding through the spine like an empty C-curve. Inhale to return. Repeat 5-8 times.',
 'Bending at the waist instead of creating a full C-curve spine (every vertebra must curve — this is spinal articulation, not a hamstring stretch), holding the breath, gripping the legs for leverage.',
 'pilates',
 array['The C-curve: imagine each vertebra separating from the one below it as you fold forward','Reach the arms forward as if pushing something away: this actively creates the spinal flexion rather than passively collapsing','This exercise mobilizes the spine after sitting and creates the hamstring flexibility needed for advanced Pilates exercises','Sitting on a blanket if the hamstrings are tight: raised hips allow the pelvis to tilt forward, enabling a longer spine'],
