 'Sit with legs wide, arms extended to the sides. Rotate toward one leg, then reach the opposite hand toward the outside of the foot in a sawing motion (3 small reaches forward). Return to center. Switch sides. 3-5 reps each side.',
 'Moving from the arms instead of the thoracic spine (the rotation must come from the ribcage), knees releasing from straight (legs stay straight and engaged throughout), letting the hips lift off the floor on the rotated side.',
 'pilates',
 array['Hips anchored equally: both sit bones press into the mat throughout — any lifting means the rotation is coming from the hips rather than the spine','The sawing motion: 3 small forward pulses while in the rotated position — these gentle pulses deepen the stretch in each breath','Waist draws in: before rotating, engage the core — the rotation happens over the top of a stable center','This is the Pilates detoxification exercise: the rotation wrings the torso like a wet towel'],
