 'Using momentum to get up instead of articulating the spine, not maintaining the V-shape at the top (spine and legs at the same angle to the floor), rounding too much in the lower back at the bottom.',
 'pilates',
 array['The Teaser is the test of Pilates mastery: if you can do a controlled Teaser, every fundamental is working','At the top: imagine a right angle — but not 90° to the floor. Rather, the body forms a V at about 45° on each side','Legs and torso move simultaneously: this requires the hip flexors and core to coordinate perfectly','Build this with: Teaser Prep (one leg only) → Teaser I (both legs in table top) → Teaser II (legs straight) → Teaser III (all in one motion)'],
