 'Lie face down, hands under shoulders, elbows bent. Engage the glutes and core. Press hands into the mat to lift the head and chest, elbows remaining at 45-60° (not straight). Hold 5 breaths. Lower slowly. Repeat 5-8 times.',
 'Crunching the lower back by lifting too high (the lift comes from back extension strength — stop at the height your back strength can control), pushing away from the mat using only arm strength, neck craning upward.',
