 array['Back muscles first: before pressing into the hands, engage the erectors and lift the chest with back strength — the hands are assistants','Glutes engaged: squeeze the glutes throughout the swan — this stabilizes the sacrum and reduces lumbar compression','Gaze forward and slightly down: the cervical spine stays long throughout','Swan prep builds to full swan dive: this progressive approach ensures the back strength exists before the full extension is attempted'],
