 'Lie on back, both legs vertical. Keeping the pelvis as stable as possible, circle both legs to the right, down and around, and back up to vertical, then to the left. 3-5 circles each direction. The circle moves the legs, not the pelvis.',
 'The pelvis rocking and rolling excessively (some pelvic movement is unavoidable at full range — control is the goal, not perfection), using momentum, making the circles too large initially.',
