 array['Start small: the first circles are small, then progressively widen as control is established in each session','Lower back pressing into the mat as the legs pass the bottom: this requires deliberate core engagement','Inhale to circle down, exhale to return: the breath assists the core engagement pattern','The corkscrew is the most demanding core-and-hip integration exercise in classical Pilates — it requires significant preparatory strength'],
