 'Sit tall with legs straight together, arms extended to the sides at shoulder height. Inhale to grow tall. Exhale to rotate the torso to one side (2-3 pulses at the end of range). Inhale to return center. Switch sides.',
 'Letting the hips rotate (must stay square and anchored — only the spine above the waist rotates), rotating from the arms (the arms are a gauge, not an engine — the ribcage drives the rotation), sitting with a rounded spine.',
 'pilates',
 array['Sit bones stay equal: if one lifts, the rotation has exceeded what the spine can manage — reduce the range','The back arm is the indicator: if the hand behind you moves sideways, the pelvis has rotated','3 small pulses at the end: each pulse seeks a tiny additional degree of rotation without the pelvis moving','This is the Pilates version of thoracic rotation training: the same movement coaches use for baseball, tennis, and golf'],
