('Pilates Push Up',
 'pectorals', array['triceps','deltoids','core'], array['pectorals','triceps','core'],
 'yoga_pilates', 'press', array['yoga_mat'], 'intermediate', true,
 'Stand tall. Walk hands down the body and onto the floor, walking out to a plank position. Do 3-5 push-ups. Walk hands back toward feet, roll up through the spine to standing. This is the full Pilates push-up sequence.',
 'Skipping the rolling down and up sequence (the walk-out and roll-up are what make this distinctly Pilates — not just a push-up), not maintaining plank alignment during the push-ups, rushing the walk-out.',
 'pilates',
 array['The sequence is the exercise: walk down → walk out → push-up × 3-5 → walk back → roll up','Each element has a purpose: the walk-down articulates the spine, the push-ups build upper body strength, the roll-up builds core and spinal mobility','The plank walk-out challenges the core as the center of gravity shifts — this is the integration, not just a push-up variation','5 complete sequences is a full set: the walking sequences are part of the exercise, not transition movements'],
 array['Pilates Push Up with Hover','Advanced Push Up with Leg Lift'],
