('Pilates Inner Thigh Lift',
 'inner_thighs', array['core','obliques'], array['inner_thighs','core'],
 'yoga_pilates', 'isolation', array['yoga_mat'], 'beginner', false,
 'Lie on your side with the top leg bent and top foot flat on the floor in front. Straighten the bottom leg. Lift the bottom leg as high as possible with the inner thigh, then lower with control. 15-20 reps each side.',
 'Bending the bottom knee (the bottom leg must remain straight), using momentum to swing the leg up, allowing the pelvis to rock.',
 'pilates',
 array['The top foot planted in front is your stability anchor: press it into the floor throughout','Bottom leg inner thigh rotates up: the big toe should face slightly toward the ceiling — this is the correct adductor alignment','Higher is not better: quality of contraction matters more than range','Inner thighs are often significantly weaker than outer hips in runners, cyclists, and desk workers — this directly corrects the imbalance'],
