 'Sit with knees bent, feet flat, hands on thighs. Inhale. Exhale to tuck the tailbone and slowly roll back until the arms are straight, creating a C-curve. Inhale to hold. Exhale to roll back up to sitting. 8-10 reps.',
 'Rolling back too far (must stop when the arms are straight — not when lying down), using momentum to return to sitting instead of the core, losing the C-curve by straightening the spine during the roll.',
 'pilates',
 array['The end position: arms straight, torso at 45° — halfway between sitting and lying. This is the goal.','C-curve maintained: chin drops slightly, tail tucks under, every vertebra rounds equally','This is the preparation for the full Roll Back and Roll Up: build months of control here before progressing','The eccentric control on the way back and the concentric on the way up build the deep abdominal strength that Pilates is famous for'],
