 array['Opposite shoulder stays grounded: this is the challenge — the shoulder anchors the spine so the rotation is pure thoracolumbar','Slow and controlled: the slower the hip roll, the more oblique engagement is required','Knees together: keeping the knees touching creates inner thigh activation as a bonus','This is the gentlest form of spinal rotation available: suitable for post-natal, post-surgical, and elderly populations'],
