 'Hold a plank position. Flex one foot. Lift the leg, point the foot, then lower to the floor. Alternate legs in a controlled rhythm. 10 reps each leg. The plank position is maintained perfectly throughout all leg movements.',
 'Allowing the hips to rock side to side with each leg lift (the core and glutes must work together to prevent any movement of the hips), not pointing the foot at the top (foot articulation is part of the Pilates exercise).',
