 array['Flex then lift, point then lower: the foot articulation (flex to lift, point to lower) is the Pilates detail that makes this exercise different from a standard leg lift plank','Hips level: place a block on the lower back — it must not fall off during either leg lift','The glute activates on the lift, the core activates throughout: these two systems must work simultaneously','This is one of the most effective posterior chain and core integration exercises in Pilates'],
