('Pilates Open Leg Rocker',
 'core', array['hamstrings','erectors','hip_flexors'], array['core','hamstrings'],
 'yoga_pilates', 'multi_joint', array['yoga_mat'], 'advanced', false,
 'Sit at the edge of the mat. Hold the ankles with both hands, legs extended to form a V-shape. Rock back to the shoulder blades, then rock forward to balance at the top. 5-8 reps.',
 'Letting go of the ankles during the rock (hands on ankles throughout — this is both the grip and the lever), bending the knees when the hamstring pull becomes strong, rolling onto the neck.',
 'pilates',
 array['Hold ankles, not toes: the ankle grip allows more control and prevents rolling too far back','Stop at the shoulder blades: the neck is not part of this roll — if you feel the neck, stop and come back higher','Legs stay straight: if the hamstrings don''t allow this yet, use a strap around the feet or practice with bent knees first','This is the dynamic version of the V-balance (teaser): the rocking teaches the balance point from both directions'],
 array['Open Leg Rocker with Twist','Advanced Open Leg Rocker'],
 array['Rolling Like a Ball','Spine Stretch Forward'],
 array['pilates','advanced','core','hamstrings','spinal_massage'],
 array['neck_injuries','osteoporosis_severe','acute_lower_back_injury'],
 'mixed', 'sagittal', false, 2, 8, null, 30, true),

('Pilates Hip Hinge with Resistance Band',
 'hamstrings', array['glutes','erectors','core'], array['hamstrings','glutes'],
 'yoga_pilates', 'hip_hinge', array['resistance_bands'], 'beginner', true,
 'Stand on a resistance band, holding both ends. Hinge at the hips while maintaining a flat back. Lower the torso to 45° or parallel, feeling the hamstring stretch. Drive the hips forward to return. 10-15 reps.',
 'Rounding the lower back (Pilates demands the same neutral spine as strength training), squatting instead of hinging, moving too quickly.',
 'pilates',
 array['Pilates applies to everyday movement: the hip hinge is one of the most important movement patterns for preventing back injury','Flat back throughout: in Pilates, a neutral spine is the foundation of all movement quality','The resistance band provides feedback: the tension increases as the hips hinge back, rewarding the correct hip-back direction','This bridges the Pilates studio and the gym: the movement quality from Pilates directly translates to safer deadlifts and stronger erectors'],
 array['Pilates Hip Hinge with Heavier Band','Deadlift with Bar'],
