('Hip 90/90 Stretch',
 'hip_flexors', array['piriformis','glutes','groin','IT_band'], array['hip_flexors','piriformis','glutes'],
 'mobility', 'stretch', array['yoga_mat'], 'beginner', false,
 'Sit with both knees bent at 90°, one in front and one to the side (creating two 90° angles). Sit tall on both sit bones. Option: fold forward over the front shin. Hold 1-3 minutes each side.',
 'Collapsing the torso forward immediately (sit tall first, assess the hip restriction, then gradually fold forward), forcing the position before the hips are ready, sitting on one hip more than the other.',
 'mobility',
 array['Both sit bones equally weighted: if one hip is much higher, place a blanket under it — asymmetric tension does not allow the hip to release','Front leg 90° and back leg 90°: this is the specific combination that accesses the anterior and posterior hip capsule simultaneously','The front hip is external rotation; the back hip is internal rotation: this one position trains both in a single setup','Hold long: 2-3 minutes per side is where connective tissue change begins to occur'],
 array['Active 90/90 Hip Transitions','90/90 with Side Lean'],
 array['Supported 90/90 on Blocks','Figure-4 Supine'],
