('World''s Greatest Stretch',
 'hip_flexors', array['hamstrings','groin','thoracic_spine','deltoids'], array['hip_flexors','hamstrings','thoracic'],
 'mobility', 'multi_joint', array['yoga_mat'], 'intermediate', true,
 'From a lunge position, place the opposite hand to the ground beside the front foot. Rotate the torso, reaching the same arm toward the ceiling. Follow with a hamstring stretch (straighten the front leg). Return and switch sides. 5 reps each side.',
 'Not rotating fully through the thoracic spine (the rotation is the key differentiator from a regular lunge stretch), rushing through the sequence, skipping the hamstring component.',
 'mobility',
 array['This single movement trains hip flexor stretch + thoracic rotation + hamstring flexibility sequentially — the most efficient stretch sequence known','Eyes follow the raised hand: this ensures the cervical spine is part of the rotation, not left behind','The hamstring component: when you straighten the front leg, sit the hips back (like a straight-leg deadlift) for maximum pull','Any warm-up for any sport: 5 reps each side of the World''s Greatest Stretch is a complete joint preparation in 2-3 minutes'],
 array['World''s Greatest Stretch with Ankle Dorsiflexion','World''s Greatest Stretch at Speed'],
 array['Modified Lunge with Torso Rotation','Hip Flexor Lunge Stretch'],
 array['mobility','full_body','hip_flexor','thoracic','warm_up'],
