('Brettzel Stretch',
 'hip_flexors', array['thoracic_spine','glutes','IT_band','pectorals'], array['hip_flexors','thoracic_spine'],
 'mobility', 'stretch', array['yoga_mat'], 'intermediate', false,
 'Lie on your side with the bottom knee bent at 90°. Hold the bottom ankle with the top hand. Bend the top knee, pulling the foot toward the glute with the bottom hand. Rotate the top shoulder toward the floor. Hold 90 seconds each side.',
 'Forcing the shoulder to the floor before the thoracic spine rotation is available (let it open gradually with each exhale), releasing the foot hold, not maintaining both knee positions.',
 'mobility',
 array['Both knees held: the bottom ankle and top foot are both held simultaneously — this dual hold creates the hip flexor stretch','Exhale to open: on each exhale, the top shoulder releases a millimetre further toward the floor — the breathing is doing the stretching','This is one of Gray Cook and Brett Jones''s most celebrated mobility exercises — named after Brett (Brettzel)','The hip flexor + thoracic rotation combination addresses the two most common movement restrictions in modern sedentary populations'],
 array['Brettzel 2.0','Brettzel with Weight on Shoulder'],
 array['Supine Twist','Pigeon Pose'],
 array['mobility','hip_flexor','thoracic_rotation','FRC','recovery'],
 array['hip_replacement','acute_lower_back_injury','shoulder_injuries_acute'],
