('Couch Stretch',
 'hip_flexors', array['quads','rectus_femoris'], array['hip_flexors','quads'],
 'mobility', 'stretch', array['yoga_mat','wall'], 'intermediate', false,
 'Kneel with one shin vertical against a wall behind you. Front foot forward. Upright torso. Hold 2-3 minutes each side. The back knee is against the wall, shin up the wall, front knee over the front foot.',
 'Allowing the torso to lean forward (the torso must be upright or even slightly extended to fully stretch the hip flexor), not having the back shin on the wall (foot flat on the floor significantly reduces the stretch).',
 'mobility',
 array['Squeeze the glute of the back leg: this posterior pelvic tilt is the key that unlocks the true hip flexor stretch','Upright torso: resist the urge to lean forward — the hip flexor only lengthens fully when the trunk is extended','This stretches the rectus femoris (the quad that also crosses the hip joint): a muscle that is impossibly tight in most desk workers and runners','Kelly Starrett popularised this stretch as essential for desk workers: it counteracts the exact shortening pattern from prolonged sitting'],
 array['Couch Stretch with Hip Extension','Couch Stretch Loaded Stretch'],
 array['Hip Flexor Lunge Stretch','Half Kneeling Hip Flexor Stretch'],
 array['mobility','hip_flexor','quad','desk_workers','runners'],
 array['knee_injuries_acute','hip_flexor_strain_acute','ankle_injuries'],
