('Pancake Stretch',
 'inner_thighs', array['hamstrings','erectors','groin'], array['inner_thighs','hamstrings'],
 'mobility', 'stretch', array['yoga_mat'], 'advanced', false,
 'Sit with legs wide in a straddle. Walk the hands forward along the floor. Lower the torso toward the floor while keeping the back as flat as possible. Hold 2-3 minutes. Progress daily toward chest to floor.',
 'Rounding the back forward (the pancake requires hip flexion with a flat spine — a rounded back means the hamstrings have hit their limit and the spine is compensating), pushing too hard too soon.',
 'mobility',
 array['Sit bone pressure: if your sit bones lift when folding forward, you''ve gone too far — back up slightly','Flat back first: the target is chest to floor WITH a flat back, not just any forward fold','Internal thigh rotation: rotate the kneecaps toward the ceiling — this accesses the inner hamstring line more completely','The pancake takes 6-24 months of consistent daily stretching to achieve for most people: patience is the practice'],
 array['Pancake with Weighted Compression','Middle Split Work'],
 array['Wide Leg Forward Fold','Straddle Sit Hold'],
 array['mobility','inner_thighs','hamstrings','advanced','flexibility'],
 array['acute_groin_injury','hamstring_tears_acute','hip_injuries'],
