('Foam Roller Thoracolumbar Junction',
 'erectors', array['QL','multifidus'], array['erectors','QL'],
 'mobility', 'extension', array['foam_roller'], 'intermediate', false,
 'Place the foam roller at the junction of the lower thoracic and upper lumbar (T12-L1 area — just above the last rib). Lie back gently. This is a transition area: slightly different from the standard thoracic rolling protocol. 5 slow breaths before moving.',
 'Applying aggressive force at this junction (T12-L1 is a stress concentration point in the spine — gentleness is mandatory), spending too long in this area without movement (unlike thoracic extension, this area benefits more from breathing than sustained compression).',
 'foam_rolling',
 array['The thoracolumbar junction (T12-L1): this is where the relatively rigid thoracic spine meets the more mobile lumbar spine — a common site of stiffness and pain','Breathing only: this is a breathing release, not a hard pressure release — 5 slow deep breaths with the roller here before moving on','Gentle extension: the slight backward extension over the roller is comfortable, not forced','This area tightens predictably during deadlift, row, and squat sessions: brief attention here post-workout prevents cumulative stiffness'],
 array['Thoracolumbar Junction Mobility Series','Combined Thoracic and Lumbar Release'],
 array['Standard Foam Roller Thoracic','Child''s Pose Release'],
