 'Letting the knee go forward of the hip (the knee should be directly below or slightly behind the hip — not in front), pulling the heel away from the body laterally (must pull straight toward the glute), compensating with a forward hip tilt.',
 'stretching',
 array['Hip extended: stand tall and push the hip of the stretched leg forward — this is the critical component that targets the hip flexor portion of the rectus femoris','Knee below hip: the lower leg should hang vertically from the knee when viewed from the side','One-hand balance: if needed, hold a wall with the opposite hand — but aim to develop the balance aspect as the stretch becomes familiar','The rectus femoris is the only quad muscle that also crosses the hip joint: this position (knee flexed + hip extended) is the only way to stretch it fully'],
