 'Stand tall. Interlace the fingers behind the back. Straighten the arms and draw the hands away from the body. Simultaneously lift the chest and gently draw the shoulder blades together. Hold 30-45 seconds.',
 'Arching the lower back (the chest lift comes from thoracic extension, not lumbar extension — engage the core to prevent the lower back from overextending), not drawing the hands far enough from the body.',
