 'mobility', 'stretch', array['step','bodyweight'], 'beginner', false,
 'Stand with the balls of both feet on the edge of a step, heels hanging off. Lower both heels below the step level slowly (gastrocnemius stretch). Hold 30-60 seconds. Option: add single-leg for increased intensity.',
 'Not controlling the descent (sudden dropping can create an Achilles injury — lower slowly over 3-5 seconds), not holding the rail (safety first — always have handrail support when stretching on a step).',
 'stretching',
 array['Slow descent: lower the heels over 3-5 seconds — the slow eccentric load is both a stretch AND a calf strengthening exercise simultaneously','Both heels level: lower both heels to the same depth to ensure symmetric calf and Achilles loading','Single-leg progression: once bilateral is comfortable, progress to single-leg which allows more control of the intensity','This is the gold-standard Achilles tendon stretch: used in both prevention and rehabilitation of Achilles tendinopathy'],
