('Hip Adductor Contract-Relax Stretch',
 'inner_thighs', array['groin','hip_adductors'], array['inner_thighs','groin'],
 'mobility', 'stretch', array['yoga_mat'], 'intermediate', false,
 'Sit in a butterfly position (soles of feet together). Press the knees into the floor using the adductors (isometric contraction of the inner thighs). Hold 7 seconds. Relax and press the knees down with the hands. The new range is your post-PNF gain. Repeat 3 cycles.',
 'Using the hands to press the knees during the contraction phase (must be the inner thigh pressing up against the hand resistance — not hands alone pressing down), confusing the direction of the contraction.',
 'stretching',
 array['The PNF sequence: knees press UP (adductors contracting) against hand resistance (7 sec) → relax → knees pressed DOWN with hands (new stretch range) → hold 20-30 sec → repeat','Both hands on both knees: provide equal resistance to both knees simultaneously — this prevents side-to-side compensation','3 cycles produces the maximum gain: by cycle 3, the butterfly range is typically 20-30% greater than at the start — a measurable and meaningful change','This is the fastest method for improving butterfly and groin flexibility: it should be prescribed before any program that requires inner thigh flexibility'],
 array['Butterfly PNF with Yoga Block','Advanced Butterfly with Forward Fold'],
 array['Static Butterfly Stretch','Supine Adductor Stretch'],
