('Overhead Lat Stretch in Doorway',
 'lats', array['teres_major','serratus'], array['lats','teres_major'],
 'mobility', 'stretch', array['bodyweight','doorway'], 'beginner', false,
 'Stand in a doorway. Grab the door frame at head height with one hand. Step backward and to the side, creating a sidebend stretch. Feel the stretch along the side body from the hip to the armpit. Hold 30-45 seconds each side.',
 'Standing too close to the doorway (must step back far enough that the arm is at an angle creating real lateral tension), not making the sidebend significant enough (must feel a stretch along the entire lateral line).',
 'stretching',
