('Lumbar Flexion Stretch (Knee Hug)',
 'erectors', array['glutes','hamstrings'], array['erectors','glutes'],
 'mobility', 'stretch', array['yoga_mat'], 'beginner', false,
 'Lie on your back. Draw both knees to the chest and hug them with both arms. Rock gently from side to side. Hold for 60-90 seconds. Then draw one knee at a time for a single-leg version. Breathe deeply throughout.',
 'Pulling the knees so hard that the lower back comes completely off the floor (some lower back rounding is normal and part of the stretch — excessive pulling that strains the neck or compresses the discs is too much), lifting the head to add to the pull.',
 'stretching',
 array['This is a gentle decompression stretch: it rounds the lower back slightly in the opposite direction of the day''s compression — not a vigorous treatment','The gentle rock: rocking side to side provides a self-massage for the sacrum and lumbar region — pairs perfectly with the static hug','Head stays down: the neck should be relaxed and long throughout — if the chin is forced to the chest, ease the pull','5 minutes before bed: this is the most effective pre-sleep stretch for lower back discomfort — it releases the day''s accumulated lumbar compression'],
 array['Dynamic Lumbar Flexion Series','Knee Hug with Spinal Twist'],
